Russian President Vladimir Putin said on Friday he needed time to decide whether he would run for another presidential term at the next election in 2018.&#8220;I will look at what&#8217;s going on in the country, in the world,&#8221; said Putin, calling a reporter who had asked him to provide reasons why people would want to vote for him again &#8220;a provocateur&#8221;.The next presidential election is due to take place in March 2018.&#8220;Taking into account what we have done, what we need to do and how, a decision will be made on whether I participate or do not participate in the upcoming elections,&#8221; said Putin.-Reuters